Obtain Straw by cutting Wheat on a Cutting Board or using a Tinkers' Sword, Dagger, or Cleaver on Tall Grass. Straw is useful for making Rope and Canvas!
Place the Carved Pumpkin on top of the Hay Bale to create a Straw Golem. He will harvest any crops and put them into a chest nearby. Feed your new Golem friend Limes to keep them happy!
Glowsticks can be thrown to light up a far away area. They will not last forever so use them wisely!
Y=0 to Y=132 and Y=265 to Y=396
Dirt can be located all over the world. If you can't find any, use a Hoe or a Mattock and Right-Click Rooted Dirt or Coarse Dirt to create Dirt!

Need slightly better armor? Cobblestone Armor is a smidgen above Wooden Armor and pretty heavy so it slows you down. But it rocks!
You're going to need to fix up your flint tools. Locate some Gravel which will allow you to make Flint. Use a Flint Repair Kit to fix up your tools.

You can use Bone Blocks to Reinforce your Tinkers' Construct Gear
Out of food? Make some Rock Soup to hold you over until you can make a real meal!

Ready to take your backpack game to the next level? Gather the materials and craft yourself a sturdy and stylish bronze backpack. With this upgraded pack on your back, you'll be able to carry all your gear and supplies with ease as you journey through the treacherous world!
Collect Cobbled Andesite, Diorite, Granite, and Cobblestone to make an upgraded Pickaxe Head!

You should be able to make a lightsource by finding glowstone on the walls and a stick from breaking Rooted Dirt.

You can hang your lantern in your Hip Curios Slot accessible from your inventory.
You can a Tinkers' Sword, Dagger, or Cleaver to use on the Cutting Board
You should be able to find wood at the top of the caves. Trees rarely spawn and there are logs in the ground.
Obtain Bark by using an Axe on a Log in-world or on a Cutting Board
The Cooking for Blockheads kitchen blocks make cooking easy! The Fridge will also stop food from spoiling!

If you don't have access to Leather, you can make a book by using Canvas which is crafted using Straw. Tree Bark can used to make Paper if you're unable to locate Sugar Cane.

Pack It Up: Time to ditch that old, tattered satchel and upgrade to a real adventurer's backpack! Gather the materials and get crafting - your hoarding habit will thank you for the extra storage space!
You'll learn the basics and how to survive in this treacherous world, but the challenges won't be easy. Are you ready to take on the first steps of your epic journey? Gather your gear and let's go!
